parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake module can cause the parking brake to engage independently, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The parking brake engages independently
the parking brake will not release
the ABS and brake warning lights illuminate
the dashboard displays "Apply Parking Brake" or "Parking Brake Fault" messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the brakes fail to engage
the ABS and brake warning lights illuminate
the dashboard displays "Brake Failure" or "ABS Fault" messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads and rotors can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pads and rotors wear down excessively
the brakes vibrate or grind
the ABS and brake warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also cause damage to property and other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the brake pedal is pressed
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed harder. The engine may race or rev loudly
and the vehicle may lurch forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Accelerator Pedal Design Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal and accelerator pedal can lead to accidental acceleration, which can cause accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The driver's foot can accidentally press both pedals simultaneously
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Master Brake Cylinder and Brake Booster Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the master brake cylinder and brake booster can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly stop or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the parking brake fails to release automatically
the vehicle stops unexpectedly
the rear wheels lock up
the vehicle jerks forward or backward
the transmission shifts roughly
and the vehicle experiences premature wear on the rear brakes and tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifts roughly
the vehicle jerks forward or backward
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
and the vehicle experiences premature wear on the transmission components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control or experience unexpected stopping, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle decelerates unexpectedly
the rear wheels lock up
and the vehicle experiences premature wear on the rear brakes and tires.
